3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX calculates NEAR/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rate is determined by the premium/discount between the perpetual contract price and the spot index, with a typical range of -0.375% to +0.375% per funding period. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while short positions pay when rates are negative. BingX applies a 0.02% maker fee and 0.05% taker fee structure that should be factored into arbitrage calculations."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","NEAR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR/USDT represents a mid-volume Layer 1 blockchain token that often exhibits distinct funding rate patterns due to its ecosystem developments and validator staking dynamics. The token's moderate volatility and established market presence create consistent funding rate opportunities, while its correlation with broader Layer 1 trends provides predictable arbitrage windows."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR/USDT funding rates on BingX typically range from -0.1% to +0.15% per 8-hour period, with spikes during ecosystem announcements or major protocol upgrades. The pair shows strong correlation with overall Layer 1 sentiment, often maintaining positive funding during bull markets as traders leverage long positions. Funding rates tend to normalize quickly after major moves, usually within 2-3 funding periods. Weekend periods often see reduced funding rate volatility due to lower trading activity and institutional absence."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes viable when BingX NEAR/USDT funding rates diverge by more than 0.05% from major exchanges like Binance or OKX. The 8-hour funding intervals provide sufficient time to establish positions across exchanges and capture rate differentials. BingX's lower liquidity can create temporary funding rate premiums during volatile periods, offering short-term arbitrage windows. Grid trading bots on BingX can be utilized to maintain delta-neutral positions while collecting funding payments."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX's lower liquidity for NEAR/USDT can result in wider spreads during volatile periods, impacting arbitrage profitability. The exchange's limited advanced order types may restrict sophisticated hedging strategies compared to tier-1 exchanges. Funding rate reversals can occur rapidly during NEAR ecosystem events or broader market shifts, requiring active position management. Cross-exchange arbitrage faces additional risks from potential withdrawal delays or network congestion during high-activity periods."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are NEAR/USDT funding rates updated on BingX?","answer":"BingX updates NEAR/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rates are calculated based on the 8-hour time-weighted average premium between the perpetual contract and spot index prices."},{"question":"What is the typical funding rate range for NEAR/USDT on BingX?","answer":"NEAR/USDT funding rates on BingX typically range from -0.1% to +0.15% per 8-hour period under normal market conditions. Extreme market events can push rates to the maximum bounds of -0.375% to +0.375% per funding period."},{"question":"Can I use BingX's copy trading for funding rate strategies?","answer":"While BingX offers copy trading features, funding rate arbitrage requires precise timing and position management that may not align well with copied strategies. It's recommended to manually execute funding rate strategies for optimal control over entry and exit points."},{"question":"How does BingX's NEAR/USDT liquidity affect funding arbitrage?","answer":"BingX's moderate NEAR/USDT liquidity can create both opportunities and risks for funding arbitrage. Lower liquidity may generate temporary funding rate premiums but can also result in wider spreads and potential slippage when establishing or closing positions."}]}]
